data.name: ReportEmployeesWithoutActiveTasks_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Users with No Open Tasks report will display a list of the users who have no open tasks at the moment. {3}{2}To view all users with no open tasks across all projects, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To select a particular group or a particular project, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportEmployment_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Workload report will display the number of tasks assigned to a user, grouped according to their status.{3}{2}To view the data for all the users, click the Generate Report button right away. {3}{2}To select a particular group or user, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportLateMilestones_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Overdue Milestones report will display a list of overdue milestones.{3}{2}To view the overdue milestones across all projects, click on Generate Report right away.{3}{2}To view the overdue milestones for a given project only, select the desired project from the drop-down list, and then click on Generate Report.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportLateTasks_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Overdue Tasks report will display a list of overdue tasks.{3}{2}To view the overdue tasks across all projects, click the Generate Report button.{3}{2}To view the overdue tasks for a given project only, select the desired project from the drop-down list below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportProjectList_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Project List report will display a list of projects.{3}{2}To view all active projects with their respective manager, number of tasks, milestones, and team members, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To view projects of a particular group and/or view both active and closed projects, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportProjectsWithoutActiveMilestones_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Projects with No Open Milestones report will display a list of projects with no open milestones attached.{3}{2}To view all projects with no open milestones, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To check such projects within a particular group or check a particular user, select the desired group and user, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportProjectsWithoutActiveTasks_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Projects with No Open Tasks report will display a list of projects with no open tasks assigned.{3}{2}To view all projects with no open tasks, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To check such projects within a particular group or check a particular user, select the desired group and/or user below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportTaskList_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Project Tasks report will display a list of tasks grouped according to the project and milestone they are attached to. {3}{2}To view the list of all tasks across all projects with the responsible person and status indicated, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To view only the tasks for a particular project or of a given status, or the tasks created over the specified number of last weeks, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportTimeSpendSummary_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Time Tracking report displays a list of users with their total work time calculated basing on a time register.{3}{2}This report helps track the total amount of time spent by a user on performing his tasks.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportUpcomingMilestones_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The Upcoming Milestones report will display a list of upcoming milestones.{3}{2}To view the upcoming milestones across all projects for a week's period, click on Generate Report right away.{3}{2}To view the upcoming milestones for a given project and/or another time period, select the desired project from the drop-down list and/or another margin date from the Time Period list first, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportUserActivity_Descripton
data.value: {0}{2}The User Activity report will display all the actions of a particular user within Projects for a given time period.{3}{2}To display your own activity for the previous week, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To set another time period or select another user, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}

data.name: ReportUserTasks_Description
data.value: {0}{2}The User Tasks report will display the list of tasks grouped according to the user they are assigned to.{3}{2}To view all tasks of users with their status indicated, click the Generate Report button right away.{3}{2}To view only the tasks for a particular user/group or of a given status, or the tasks created over the specified number of last weeks, configure the report parameters below, and then click the Generate Report button.{3}{1}
